                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/2983: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ramer</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-11-23T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 23, 1923—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>52. Your November 20, 2 p.m.</p>
                <p>Inform President Martinez, if you have not already done so, that the Department’s
                    offer to pay expenses of electoral experts was made simply in a desire to
                    relieve the Nicaraguan Government of the financial burden involved, but that
                    there would of course be no objection should the Nicaraguan Government wish to
                    pay the expense itself.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
